# 🧠 OS Concept 1: Database Indexing Basics

## 1️⃣ Simple Idea

Index helps database find data faster.

Without index:

👉 database scans every row.

With index:

👉 database jumps directly to needed data.

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Book index 📖

Instead of reading whole book:

👉 directly jump to page number.

---

## ⚙️ Example

Without index:

```text id="j7x1mk"
Search user among 1 million rows
```

Slow ❌

---

With index:

```text id="9m4zrp"
Direct lookup
```

Fast ✔

---

## Why Important?

Indexes improve:

✔ search speed
✔ query performance

But:

❌ extra storage needed
❌ writes become slower

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why indexing improves performance?**

👉 Because it reduces full-table scanning.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="x5q2vn"
Index = shortcut to data
```

